      "comment_id" : 65391683,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@KevinDay Actually I think your &#39;mvc&#39; is a bit outdated/shortsighted. Yes, its nice to have view/model separation, however, sometimes you do need to pass data through your jsp (like to a js file), and creating a whole bunch of infrastructure to stay &#39;mvc&#39; is not the sane answer. I&#39;m all for doing things the correct way, but sometimes its good to remember that the approaches that were good in your day may not be so good anymore."
