      "body" : "@smaudet Some would say using JSP in 2016 is a stupid thing :) with the quality of Component Oriented Java UI frameworks available these days: Wicket, JSF, Tapestry are some Java Component Oriented UI frameworks. Angular 2 is really showing that Component Oriented UIs are really a &#39;thing&#39; now but it means writing your UI in a completely different language (JS, Coffee or TypeScript) to your server side code. Most good Java component oriented frameworks can deliver the same yummy goodness that Angular 2 delivers but in a single language, easy to develop, understand, debug and maintain solution."
