      "comment_id" : 71955582,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Sorry but I have to add that this &quot;using a list is breaking MVC&quot; is just nonsense. Whether you use tag libs or not you are still just doing the exact same thing, it&#39;s just that the tag lib hides the &quot;List&quot; syntax from you. There is always a &quot;static dependency&quot; between the view and the model. You can hardly write a view for a model without a dependency because the view is always specifically for that model! If you render the model in multiple places and want to have minimal code changes if the model changes then you just use a partial view (which is of course what a custom tag would be!)"
    } ],
